endix. Plessner's Collected Writings (Gesammelte Schriften) -- tAbout the Authors -- tName Index -- tSubject Index0 aOpen Accessuhttps://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_abf2funrestricted online access2star  aHelmuth Plessner (1892-1985) was one of the founders of philosophical anthropology, and his book The Stages of the Organic and Man, first published in 1928, has inspired generations of philosophers, biologists, social scientists, and humanities scholars. This volume offers the first substantial introduction to Plessner's philosophical anthropology in English, not only setting it in context with such familiar figures as Bergson, Cassirer, and Merleau-Ponty, but also showing Plessner's relevance to contemporary discussions in a wide variety of fields in the humanities and sciences.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBiologyxPhilosophyvCongresses. 0aBiologyxPhilosophyxCongresses. 0aPhilosophical anthropologyvCongresses. 0aPhilosophical anthropologyxCongresses. 4aHistory, Art History, and Archaeology. 4aPhilosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Criticism.2bisacsh  aPlessner, philosophical anthropology, culture, technology, eccentricity.1 aBoccignone, Martino Enrico, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBuuren, Jasper van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoolen, Maarten, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDelitz, Heike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEbke, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aErnste, Huib, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFischer, Joachim, econtributor.4ct